http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Action-plan-to-promote-tourism-in-Kurnool/article13993607.ece

District Collector Ch. Vijayamohan said on Sunday that an action plan would be formulated to promote tourism in Kurnool district.Addressing officials in a meeting on tourism promotion at the State guest house here, Mr. Vijayamohan told officials to finalise tourism packages from Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Kurnool covering significant temples, tourist and historic places in Kurnool district.He announced constitution of a three-member committee with District Revenue Officer G.S. Gangadhar Goud, Assistant Commissioner of Endowments Venkateswarlu and District Tourism Officer B. Venkateswarlu to inspect the routes and facilities such as availability of accommodation, food and darsan to the tourists.On the directions of Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu and Deputy Chief Minister K.E. Krishnamurthy to give a fillip to tourism, tourist packages were sought to be introduced from January 26, the Collector said. One to three night tourist packages were being formulated with the help of private tourist agencies, he added.